<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <style>
        /* Reset margin and padding */
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        /* Full height body and html for flexbox layout */
        html,
        body {
            height: 100%;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
            color: #333;
        }

        /* Flexbox layout for body to make footer stick to the bottom */
        body {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: space-between; /* Ensure footer stays at the bottom */
        }

        /* Main content area */
        .container {
            flex: 1;
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            text-align: center; /* Center text in the container */
        }

        /* Header Section */
        header {
            background-color: #861e9b;
            color: rgb(0, 0, 0);
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            margin: 0;
        }

        /* Paragraph styling */
        p {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            text-align: center; /* Center all paragraphs */
            padding-left: 30px;  /* Adds space on the left */
            padding-right: 30px; /* Adds space on the right */
            max-width: 700px;  /* Ensure paragraphs do not exceed this width */
            margin: 20px auto;  /* Center the paragraphs */
        }

        h2 {
            margin-top: 40px;
            text-align: center; /* Center the "Services" heading */
        }

        /* Footer Styling */
        footer {
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        /* Styling for unordered list */
        ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            padding-left: 20px;
            text-align: left; /* Align the list items to the left */
            margin: 20px auto;
            max-width: 700px; /* Ensure the list doesn't exceed a max width */
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        /* Add any additional styling for the image */
        .service-image {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 750px;
            display: block;
            margin: 20px auto; /* Center the image */
        }
    </style>

</head>

<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar1.ejs') %>
        <h2>Services Provided</h2>

        <img src="/public/images/massage types.png" alt="Massage Types" class="service-image">

        <p>
            The importance of each type of massage varies depending on the individual's needs and conditions. Here's how each type of massage can help you:
        </p>


        <ul id="bulletList">
            <li>
                <strong>Massage:</strong> Focuses on the muscles of the back, neck, and shoulders to relieve tension,
                improve posture, and reduce discomfort. It can be a relaxing treatment or aimed at alleviating pain or
                stiffness in the back area.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Sport Massage:</strong> Designed for athletes or active individuals, this massage helps improve
                performance, prevent injuries, and reduce muscle soreness. It involves techniques like stretching, deep
                pressure, and kneading to target muscle groups used in sports.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Deep Tissue Massage:</strong> Uses slow, firm strokes and deep pressure to target the deeper
                layers of muscle and connective tissue. It's effective for chronic pain, muscle tension, and stiff
                areas, particularly in the neck, shoulders, and back.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Pregnancy Massage:</strong> A safe, gentle massage tailored to the needs of pregnant women,
                usually after the first trimester. It helps alleviate common pregnancy discomforts like back pain,
                swelling, and stress while improving relaxation and circulation.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Couple Massage:</strong> A shared experience where two people receive massages at the same time
                in the same room. It's ideal for couples or friends who want to enjoy relaxation together, often in a
                spa setting.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Mobile Massage:</strong> A service where a massage therapist comes to your location, such as
                home, hotel, or office. This type of massage offers convenience and flexibility, often for relaxation or
                stress relief, without needing to visit a spa.
            </li>
        </ul>
</body>

<footer>
    <%- include('partials/footer.ejs') %>
</footer>

</html>